wordcloud 표현하기¶

  • 설치 : pip install wordcloud
  • 참고 : https://wikidocs.net/172882

워드 클라우드 기본¶

실습1¶

In [19]:
from wordcloud import WordCloud
from konlpy.tag import Komoran
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from konlpy.corpus import kolaw   

# 대상 텍스트 데이터 
kolaw.fileids()                          
para = kolaw.open('constitution.txt').read()
tagger = Komoran()
nouns = tagger.nouns(para)
In [22]:
nouns[:4]
Out[22]:
['대한민국', '헌법', '역사', '전통']
In [25]:
# 리스트를 문자열로 바꾸기
text = ", ". join(nouns)
text[:4]
Out[25]:
'대한민국'
In [26]:
# 클라우딩 객체 설정
my_path='fonts/NanumMyeongjoExtraBold.ttf'
wordcloud = WordCloud(font_path=my_path, 
                      background_color='white', 
                      width=1200, 
                      height=800).generate(text)
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
plt.axis('off')
Out[26]:
(-0.5, 1199.5, 799.5, -0.5)

그림을 아래와 같이 넘파이 배열로 데이터를 변환시킴¶

In [3]:
import numpy as np
from PIL import Image
icon = Image.open('images/korea_map.png').convert("RGBA")
mask = Image.new("RGB", icon.size, (255,255,255))
mask.paste(icon, icon)
mask = np.array(mask)

그림을 배경으로 워드 클라우딩을 그기기¶

In [4]:
my_path='fonts/NanumMyeongjoExtraBold.ttf'
wordcloud = WordCloud(font_path=my_path, 
                      background_color='white', 
                      width=240, 
                      height=200,
                      mask=mask).generate(text)
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(14,10))
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
plt.axis('off')
Out[4]:
(-0.5, 499.5, 499.5, -0.5)

import numpy as np
from PIL import Image

icon = Image.open("images/heart.png").convert("RGBA")
mask = Image.new("RGB", icon.size, (255,255,255))
mask.paste(icon,icon)
mask = np.array(mask)
wordcloud = WordCloud(font_path=my_path, 
                      background_color='white', 
                      width=1200, 
                      height=800,
                     mask= mask).generate(text)
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
plt.axis('off')
Out[13]:
(-0.5, 1199.5, 1096.5, -0.5)
